It’s here - the Lydia x Arena signature orca suit 🌟⚜️🔱 celebrating 50 years of @arenawaterinstinct 

I chose the orca whale for my signature collection because they are an animal I’ve always been fascinated with. People think of sharks as being the top of the marine food chain, but orcas can actually overpower them. They’re underestimated in that respect - beautiful and badass - they have the name killer whale for a reason. Growing up in Alaska, I watched them swim majestically around Resurrection Bay, and there is no other animal I would want to represent me.

I’m thrilled to introduce a collab that’s been in the works for a long time now - the Resurrection Bay Blend in partnership with Kaladi Brothers Coffee and Bethany Waggoner to support Seward Arts Council!

Ever since the Olympics I’ve wanted to work with @kaladibrotherscoffee . When the opportunity arose to support one of my favorite organizations, work with one of my favorite brands, and have one of my favorite artists paint me as a mermaid @bee.swag , I was beyond excited.

The Seward Arts Council is a 100% volunteer-run non-profit whose mission is to foster appreciation, education, and understanding of the arts by promoting cultural opportunities, performances, instruction, and exhibitions. They proudly support Seward Mural Society, Port City Players, Community Band, Seward Artists in Schools, Seward Music & Arts Festival, First Friday Art Walk, and various art scholarships.

$5 per coffee bag sale will be donated to support them and their purpose in Alaska. This medium roast blend has low acidity and reminds us of home with notes of maple, dark chocolate, and warming spice! Get a bag while supplies last at Kaladi.com!

“Water is a reflection of the cycle of life, with its ebbs and flows, highs and lows” -Unknown 🌚🍃💧

You may remember Lydia Jacoby from the 2020 Tokyo Olympics, where she took home both a gold and a silver medal. At 19, the Alaska native is just getting started and joins the Glamour College Women of the Year class of 2023. In conversation with fellow pro swimmer, Olympic gold medalist, and world champion Simone Manuel, Jacoby talks about what it feels like to win a gold medal, the importance of having a female coach, and why pursuing her passions outside the pool has been invaluable. Learn more about the University of Texas at Austin swimmer and #CWOTY2023 at the link in bio. 

Photography by @helmvisuals / Getty Images / Jasmine Durhal / Design by @artchanning
